</PARA>

<PARA>
<Emphasis remap="it">i386</Emphasis> and <Emphasis remap="it">alpha</Emphasis> are little endian, <Emphasis remap="it">arm</Emphasis> can choose (but the NetWinder has been wired as a little endian machine). <Emphasis remap="it">m68k</Emphasis>, <Emphasis remap="it">sparc</Emphasis> and <Emphasis remap="it">ppc</Emphasis> are big-endian! <Emphasis remap="it">mips</Emphasis> can choose I think. If unsure, look in <filename>/usr/src/linux/asm/byteorder.h</filename> and check if it includes <command>&lt;linux/byteorder/big_endian.h&gt;</command> or <command>&lt;linux/byteorder/little_endian.h&gt;</command> .
</PARA>

